title: For Sale:  1915 Remington Model 8 in 30 Remington
postcontent: As titled, this is a John Browning design, produced by Remington, and one of the first semi auto rifles ever made.  Has an original Marbles tang sight as well (lists for around $200-250 on some sites). Also have 2 of the original stripper clips for this gun (very hard to find!). I have fired about 100 rounds through it, works as it should.  It's a take down rifle, can be stored in a small case for transport.  No cracks in the wood, only minor dings, as expected for a 103 year old hunting rifle.  The price includes 5 boxes of original commercial and antique ammo, the Peters ammo (3 boxes) was specially made for Remington model 8, the later model 81, and model 14 and 141 rifles. I have about 35 rounds of reloads (I reloaded the ammo made by PCI and Reeds, never shot the vintage ammo) plus another few boxes of ammo made recently by PCI and Reeds ammunition of OKc.  So, there's plenty of brass here for reloading as the 30 Remington is no longer commercially produced (although PCI and Reeds still produces the round, we are fortunate to have Reeds ammunition so close in OKC).  A version of this rifle was used by Frank Hamer to end Bonnie and Clyde's run, so besides being a John Browning design it has historical significance for other reasons.  Easily reloaded using 30-30 data, I use a Lee Classic Loader (can be obtained for $35 or so on eBay) and have enjoyed this rifle, but I want to move on to other firearm endeavors, otherwise I would keep this little rifle as it has been a unique piece in my collection and a conversation starter at the range.  These have been listed on other sites for this price just for the gun, but with this you would get ammo and brass without having to do anything but provide the other common components.  Serious inquiries only.
